Diagnoses. Male imago.
1) stigmatic area of forewing hyaline (
Figs 4J and 4K
); 2) hind wing absent; 3) abdominal terga and sterna I–VI white and VII–X brown (
Fig. 4F
); 4) posterior margin of styliger plate convex, with pointed spine medially (
Fig. 4H
); 5) posterior margin of styliger plate with one rounded protuberance projected ventrally (

Fig. 
4I

).

